definitions.definition: To push slightly ; to move or shake with a push or jerk , as to gain the attention of; to jolt .

examples: I tried desperately to jog my memory.

definitions.definition: To walk or ride forward with a jolting pace ; to move at a heavy pace, trudge ; to move on or along .
To move at a pace between walking and running , to run at a leisurely pace.
examples: I saw her jogging in the forest yesterday.

definitions.definition: To cause to move at an energetic trot .
To straighten stacks of paper by lightly tapping against a flat surface .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To push slightly ; to move or shake with a push or jerk , as to gain the attention of; to jolt .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To shake , stir or rouse .
( intransitive ) To walk or ride forward with a jolting pace ; to move at a heavy pace, trudge ; to move on or along .
( exercise , intransitive ) To move at a pace between walking and running , to run at a leisurely pace.
( transitive ) To cause to move at an energetic trot .
( transitive ) To straighten stacks of paper by lightly tapping against a flat surface .
